This paper deals with a source coding problem over broadcast channels, which is a fundamental problem in information theory (cs.IT) and network information theory (cs.NI). The paper also discusses graph families and their properties, which falls under the category of graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of linear programming (LP) is a key technique in this paper, which is a common tool in optimization and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of side information and its impact on the broadcast rate, which is a topic in information theory and signal processing (cs.SI).
